🍑 String Methods 
○ string_name.string_method(arguments)

📝 Formatting Methods
○ .lower()
○ .upper()
○ .title()
✎ Use case: Music Platform > Digitizing albums  > changing the album titles from lowercase to UPPERCASE or Title 

💎 Splitting Strings I
○ .split()
✎ Use case: YouTube Comments > What is the most used word in 2024? > "This video is weird" > "This", "video", "is", "weird"

💎 Splitting Strings II
○ .split('')
✎ Use case: Music Platform > Make a list of all the last names of artists > "Dua Lipa, Tauren Wells, Chris Tomlin" > "Lipa", "Wells", "Tomlin"

artists = "Dua Lipa, Tauren Wells, Chris Tomlin"

#𝘴𝘱𝘭𝘪𝘵 𝘪𝘯𝘵𝘰 𝘢 2𝘋 𝘭𝘪𝘴𝘵
artist_names = artist.split(',')
print(artist_names) >> "Dua Lipa", "Tauren Wells", "Chris Tomlin"

#𝘮𝘢𝘬𝘦 𝘢 𝘭𝘪𝘴𝘵 𝘰𝘧 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘭𝘢𝘴𝘵 𝘯𝘢𝘮𝘦𝘴
#𝘦𝘮𝘱𝘵𝘺 𝘭𝘪𝘴𝘵
artist_last_names = [] 
#𝘭𝘰𝘰𝘱 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘢𝘳𝘵𝘪𝘴𝘵_𝘯𝘢𝘮𝘦𝘴
for name in artist_names:
  #𝘶𝘴𝘦 𝘢𝘱𝘱𝘦𝘯𝘥 + 𝘴𝘱𝘭𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘮𝘢𝘬𝘦 𝘢 𝘯𝘦𝘸 𝘭𝘪𝘴𝘵
  artist_last_names.append(name.split()[-1])
print(artist_last_names) >> "Lipa", "Wells", "Tomlin" 
